In [124]:
C, S, K, SectionSize, SPLIT, DIST, selected_courses = update_parameters("project_test1.txt")
selected_courses, course_assigments, course_enrollment = determine_courses(C, S, K, SectionSize, SPLIT, DIST)

labels, values = zip(*selected_courses)
indexes = np.arange(len(labels))
width = 1

plt.bar(indexes, values, width)
plt.xticks(indexes + width * 0.5, labels)
plt.xlabel("Course Number")
plt.ylabel("Number of Students")
plt.title("Course Assignments with Uniform Distribution")
plt.show()

C, S, K, SectionSize, SPLIT, DIST, selected_courses = update_parameters("project_test1.txt")
selected_courses, course_assigments, course_enrollment = determine_courses(C, S, K, SectionSize, SPLIT, DIST)

Timing¶

Times shown in outputs from this section are inaccurate. I was accidentally overwriting the times of each method with the one that came after it (used same variable names). I realized the problem after seeing that the times were the same. They are fixed here, but for the sake of time, I did not run code to get outputs for non-timing focused results.
